FEMALE ABDOMEN (
Fig. 12
). Posterior margin of tergite 7 entire or slightly emarginate medially. Medial part of tergite 8 elongate (length ~1.5–3.0 × width), with anterior margin rounded (some specimens with posterior half poorly sclerotized and difficult to see). Epiproct diamond-shaped. Cercus as long as epiproct, with elongate preapical seta. Sternite 7 entire. Spermathecae cup-shaped and short, with sclerotized duct ~3.5 × length of spermatheca.
